It also means you'll do more overall damage, even if it's a light damage weapon. Consider; if you do 30 damage when you hit with a weapon that only lets you TRY to hit once every three seconds, your overall damage is less than a weapon that does 15 and lets you try to hit every second... more overall hits means more overall damage. This is the principal that rogue combat is founded upon.<br>
A whip is a nice, fast slashing weapon; some variation of a whip would be a good place to start.<br>
My 2 cents.<br>
